# Page static-site export feature

Renders the **clicked page and all descendant pages** to a static HTML site with **Hugo**, then
returns the rendered `public/` folder as a zip download.

## Endpoints

| Layer | Location |
|-------|----------|
| Route | `GET /apps/collectives/{collectiveId}/pages/{pageId}/export` |
| Route name | `collectiveExport#download` in `appinfo/routes.php` |
| Controller | `lib/Controller/CollectiveExportController.php` |
| Orchestration | `lib/Service/CollectiveExportService.php` (`createStaticSiteZip`) |
| Hugo runner | `lib/Service/HugoService.php` |
| Embedded theme | `lib/Service/Hugo/skeleton/` (layouts + render hooks) |

Frontend URL (not yet wired into the UI):

```js
generateUrl(`/apps/collectives/${collectiveId}/pages/${pageId}/export`)
```

## Hugo binary (`HugoService`)

- Path resolved from app config `collectives` → `hugo_binary`, else looked up in `$PATH`
  (and common bin dirs). Throws `MissingDependencyException` if missing.
- Install in the container, e.g. `apt-get install hugo`, or
  `occ config:app:set collectives hugo_binary --value=/usr/bin/hugo`.
- Build runs via `proc_open` (array command, no shell). `HOME`/`TMPDIR`/`cacheDir` are pointed
  inside the temp site dir so the web user can write Hugo's cache.

## Export scope (`CollectiveExportService::createStaticSiteZip`)

Resolve scope from the **page file** on disk, then populate `content/`:

1. **Landing page** (`isLandingPage`) → whole collective folder as the site root (`writeBranch`)
2. **Index page** in subfolder (`isIndexPage` && !landing) → that folder as the site root
3. **Leaf page** (single `.md`) → `_index.md` + attachments + sibling `{basename}/` subpage tree

### Content mapping

- `Readme.md` (index) → `_index.md` (branch bundle); folder title as frontmatter `title`
- Leaf `Title.md` → page bundle `slug/index.md` (slug = `slugify(title)`, deduped per dir)
- Subfolder `Title/` → recurse into `slug/`
- **Attachments**: `.attachments.{fileId}/` is copied next to its page as `attachments.{fileId}/`
  (Hugo ignores dot-prefixed dirs). Markdown refs are rewritten `.attachments.{id}/` →
  `attachments.{id}/` in `rewriteAttachmentLinks()`.

### Embedded theme (`Hugo/skeleton`)

- `hugo.toml` is generated per-export (title, `relativeURLs=true`, goldmark `unsafe=true`).
- Layouts: `baseof.html` (inline CSS + sidebar nav via `partials/tree.html`), `single.html`, `list.html`.
- Render hooks: `render-image.html` resolves relative images to published page resources
  (`.Page.Resources.GetMatch`); `render-link.html` turns relative `*.md` links into `*/`.

## Skipped nodes (`shouldSkipNode`)

- `.templates` (`TemplateService::TEMPLATE_FOLDER`)
- All other dot entries (attachments are copied per-page, not via the directory walk)

## Testing

```bash
# Requires auth + hugo installed in the container; example:
curl -u admin:admin -o out.zip \
  "http://localhost/index.php/apps/collectives/1/pages/133/export"
unzip -l out.zip   # contains index.html + nested page HTML + attachments.{id}/...
```

You can smoke-test the embedded theme directly by copying `Hugo/skeleton/layouts`, writing a
generated `hugo.toml`, populating `content/`, and running `hugo` (use an absolute `cacheDir`).

## Limitations / extending

- **Public shares**: would need `PublicCollectiveExportController` + token auth (not implemented)
- **Async/large exports**: synchronous in-request; huge collectives may need a background job
- Subpage **ordering** (`subpageOrder`) is not applied; Hugo orders by its defaults
- Non-image attachment links (e.g. PDFs) are not auto-published unless referenced as images
- Do not change scope to full collective unless explicitly requested
